    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-05-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-05-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="814"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d814">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">690D.91/5–1254</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Deputy Assistant Secretary of State for Near
                        Eastern, South Asian, and African Affairs</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_JJD1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Jernegan</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d814fn1">Sent through the Executive
                        Secretariat.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-05-12">May 12,
                            1954</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>Subject:</head>
                    <item>Recent Exchange of Letters Between Prime Ministers <persName
                            corresp="#p_AM2">Mohammed Ali</persName> of Pakistan and <persName
                            corresp="#p_NJ1">Nehru</persName> of India Regarding the Kashmir Dispute
                        and Military Assistance to Pakistan.</item>
                </list>
                <p>With a top secret letter dated April 3, 1954 to you, Ambassador <persName
                        corresp="#p_HHA1">Hildreth</persName> transmitted a file of correspondence
                    containing copies of a recent exchange of nineteen letters between Prime
                    Ministers <persName corresp="#p_AM2">Mohammed Ali</persName> of Pakistan and
                        <persName corresp="#p_NJ1">Nehru</persName> of India. The file was given to
                    the Ambassador by Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_AM2">Ali</persName> with
                    the request that only top Department officials have access to it.</p>
                <p>A summary of the correspondence (Tab A)<note n="2" xml:id="d814fn2">Not printed.
                        With respect to correspondence between the Prime Ministers, see footnote 2,
                            <ref target="#pg_1344">p. 1344</ref>.</note> has been prepared for your
                    use.</p>
                <p>Highlights of the correspondence are: <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>
                            <persName corresp="#p_AM2">Ali</persName>’s vigorous attempt to have
                            Admiral Nimitz retained as Kashmir Plebiscite Administrator, <persName
                                corresp="#p_NJ1">Nehru</persName>’s refusal and <persName
                                corresp="#p_AM2">Ali</persName>’s acquiescence to <persName
                                corresp="#p_NJ1">Nehru</persName>’s position.</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>
                            <persName corresp="#p_NJ1">Nehru</persName>’s suggestion of a regional
                            plebiscite in Kashmir, <persName corresp="#p_AM2">Ali</persName>’s
                            contention that the regions should be defined before any plebiscite,
                                <persName corresp="#p_NJ1">Nehru</persName>’s position that the
                            regions could properly be defined only after a plebiscite—no agreement
                            reached.</item>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>
                            <persName corresp="#p_NJ1">Nehru</persName>’s vigorous objections to
                            U.S. military assistance to Pakistan, <persName corresp="#p_AM2"
                                >Ali</persName>’s unsuccessful efforts to answer them and <persName
                                corresp="#p_NJ1">Nehru</persName>’s firm position that further
                            progress on the Kashmir issue is not now possible.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
            </div>
